                <pb facs="0718" n="696" xml:id="pg_696"/>
                <p rend="flushleft">I. <hi rend="italic">Report by the Deputies</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Council heard the Deputies’ Report tabled by the acting Chairman and
                    instructed the Deputies to complete the examination of the questions still
                    outstanding in the draft treaty with Finland.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">II. <hi rend="italic">Danube</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Council considered the U.K. Delegation’s proposal (<gloss target="#t_CFM461">C.F.M.(46)</gloss> 148).<note n="96" xml:id="d217fn96">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_629">p. 629</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The French Delegation proposed an amendment to the first paragraph (<gloss target="#t_CFM461">C.F.M.(46)</gloss> 172).<note n="97" xml:id="d217fn97">See footnote 91, <ref target="#pg_686">p. 686</ref>.</note> The Council
                    deferred discussion of the question.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">III. <hi rend="italic">Peace Treaty With Italy</hi>
                </p>
                <p>1. <hi rend="italic">Reparation</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Views were exchanged on this question.</p>
                <p>2. <hi rend="italic">Italian Navy</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Council decided to leave to Italy cruisers “Duca Degli Abruzzi, Garibaldi,
                    Montecuccoli and Cadorna” and destroyers “Da Recco, Grecale and 2 type
                    Artigliere”.</p>
                <p>The Council instructed the Naval Experts Committee to continue its study of the
                    question of the allocation of surplus units, dealing first with allocation to
                    Greece and Yugoslavia and then to the four Powers, in accordance with the
                    Ministers’ decision of April 27th.</p>
                <p>3. <hi rend="italic">Italo-Yugoslav frontier and Trieste</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Views were exchanged on this question.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">IV. <hi rend="italic">Date of the Peace Conference</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Views were exchanged on this question.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">V. <hi rend="italic">Next Meeting</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Monday 1st July, 1946, at 4 p.m. Agenda: Italo-Yugoslav frontier and Trieste,
                    Italian Colonies, date of the Peace Conference, German questions.</p>
